# aero-fighters-v2 — local environment template
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in values for local dev.
# .env.local is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
#
# See SPEC §8 Secret & Key Management for the canonical fetch flow:
#   op item get "aero-fighters-v2/google-maps-tiles-api-key" --field credential
#
# Release: aero-fighters-v2-photorealistic-inhauma-v1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED: Google Map Tiles API key (Photorealistic 3D Tiles)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create your GCP project, enable "Map Tiles API", generate a key restricted
# to Map Tiles API v1, and IP-restrict it to your home/dev IPs (SPEC §8).
# Store the key in 1Password as: aero-fighters-v2/google-maps-tiles-api-key
# Rotation cadence: quarterly, or immediately on suspected leak.
GOOGLE_MAPS_TILES_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Offline tile cache (NFR-V2-02, RR-V2-07, LD-22)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default ON: serve tiles from the offline cache built by Tools/tile-cache-populate.py.
# This means dev sessions spend $0 against the $20/month GCP cap (NFR-V2-02).
# Set to 0 only when you explicitly want to test live tile streaming.
CESIUM_OFFLINE_TILES=1

# Path to the populated tile cache.
# Defaults to ~/aero-fighters-v2-tile-cache/ if unset.
# Run Tools/tile-cache-populate.py to build the cache before first use.
# CESIUM_TILE_CACHE_DIR=$HOME/aero-fighters-v2-tile-cache

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: UE 5.5 install path
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Only needed if your UE 5.5 install is in a non-standard location.
# Standard Linux path after building from source: /opt/UnrealEngine-5.5
# Standard Windows path (forward slashes work in bash): C:/Program Files/Epic Games/UE_5.5
# UE_INSTALL_PATH=/opt/UnrealEngine-5.5
